Food Studies Ephemera Collection
Fales Library
MSS.310
7 Linear Feet
circa 1900-2010 The Food Studies Ephemera Collection consists of pamphlets, recipe booklets, and other food- and cookery-related ephemera donated to Fales by various donors.
Conditions Governing Use
Copyright (or related rights to publicity and privacy) for materials in this collection was not transferred to New York University. Permission to use materials must be secured from the copyright holder. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.
Conditions Governing Access
Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.
Provenance
The items in the Food Studies Ephemera Collection have been donated to NYU by a number of individuals from the general public. The Collection continues to expand as donations continue.
Scope and Content
The Food Studies Ephemera Collection consists of printed ephemera (primarily pamphlets and recipe booklets) having to do with food and cookery. The bulk of the materials are from the mid-twentieth century.
Arrangement
The Collection is arranged alphabetically by subject. Because the Collection will continue to expand, there are no permanent box numbers.
